Требуемый опыт работы: 1–3 годаПолная занятость, полный день




Расти, развивайся и меняй мир к лучшему вместе с нами.


ABOUT THIS JOB Our panel is the center and one of the critical components of the research. In this job of supporting the business from panel management and panel health perspective - you’ll play an important role in Retail Measurement Service (RMS), you will work on maintaining the quality of RMS panel and will have a chance to improve/optimize current work routine. You will also have close connections with other departments and colleagues from different countries to create a new best practice. RESPONSIBILITIES:  Own all activities related to database maintenance, including testing new tools, deployment of fixes and partnering with Technologies;  Execute action plans, monitor execution for local input and make recommendations to Panel Manager;   Optimize and improve existing local tools and also prepare recommendations for changes in Global practices.   ​​​A LITTLE BIT ABOUT YOU You are very attentive to details and interested in work with big data sets. You know how to clean up messy/”dirty” data and come up with a clean and insightful data set, or even go beyond to unlock new opportunities and new ways of working for your tasks and as well as your colleagues tasks with your creativity. You also enjoy working with people from different cultures and disciplines, believe that teamwork is the key to accomplish big goals and you always contribute to that vision. REQUIREMENTS:   Bachelor's degree required; Prefer graduate degree in statistical, mathematical, or technical field   English level (written and oral) from Upper-intermediate and above   Python/R, SQL as a plus   Analytical skills, attention to details and ability to connect the dots, “can do” attitude   COMPENSATION:  Competitive salary; Well-known global company; Notebook and two additional screens; Corporate discounts in fitness club World Class; Equipped Kitchens; Coffee-points and relax zones; Prime-cafe for Nielsen employees only; The young team of professionals; Free-time clubs (Book Club, Travel Club, Music Club); Social events and sports activities;
